@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Help";
}

<div class="space-y-6">
    <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold">What is Harpyx?</h1>
            <hr />
            <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                Harpyx is a multi-tenant knowledge platform for organizing workspaces and projects, ingesting documents,
                indexing content, and enabling retrieval/chat workflows with role-based collaboration.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                The following sections explain in detail the main components of the platform infrastructure and how they interact.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="card h-full bg-base-100 shadow">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h2 class="card-title">Core Concepts</h2>
                <div class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                    Harpyx is structured in layers. Understanding this model helps avoid configuration mistakes and clarifies where
                    permissions, resources and collaboration boundaries are applied.
                </div>
                <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                    <table class="table table-sm">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Concept</th>
                                <th>Meaning</th>
                                <th>Example</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td><span class="badge badge-outline">Tenant</span></td>
                                <td>Security and ownership boundary. Users can belong to one or more tenants.</td>
                                <td>Customer, business unit, or team domain.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><span class="badge badge-outline">Workspace</span></td>
                                <td>Logical container inside a tenant to organize projects.</td>
                                <td>Marketing, Legal, Support.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><span class="badge badge-outline">Project</span></td>
                                <td>Operational unit where files are processed and queried.</td>
                                <td>Q1 Policies, Product Docs, Contract Set.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><span class="badge badge-outline">Document</span></td>
                                <td>Source file ingested, parsed, chunked and indexed for retrieval/chat.</td>
                                <td>PDF, DOCX/TXT export, knowledge article.</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
                <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
                    <p><span class="font-semibold">Hierarchy:</span> Tenant contains Workspaces, Workspaces contain Projects, Projects contain Documents.</p>
                    <p><span class="font-semibold">Operational impact:</span> always confirm the correct tenant/workspace before creating or moving resources.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card h-full bg-base-100 shadow">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h2 class="card-title">Permissions Model</h2>
                <div class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                    Permissions are tenant-scoped: your current tenant (top-right switcher) defines what you can view, edit, or manage
                    across Members, Workspaces, Projects and related APIs. The same user can be Owner in one tenant and Viewer in another.
                </div>
                <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                    <table class="table table-sm">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Role</th>
                                <th>Typical Capabilities</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td><span class="font-semibold">Tenant Owner</span></td>
                                <td>Full tenant control, member management and delegation.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><span class="font-semibold">Tenant Manager</span></td>
                                <td>Member management and delegation, without owner-level governance actions.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><span class="font-semibold">Workspace Manager</span></td>
                                <td>Can manage workspaces and downstream project operations within the current tenant.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><span class="font-semibold">Project Contributor</span></td>
                                <td>Can create/update project content (for example document workflows) but not member governance.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><span class="font-semibold">Reviewer</span></td>
                                <td>Read-focused role with chat usage and limited modification powers.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td><span class="font-semibold">Viewer</span></td>
                                <td>Visibility role for consultation with minimal operational permissions.</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
                <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
                    <p><span class="font-semibold">Least privilege:</span> assign the minimum role needed for each member responsibility.</p>
                    <p><span class="font-semibold">Delegation:</span> delegated member management is controlled and revocable, not implicit.</p>
                    <p><span class="font-semibold">Cross-tenant isolation:</span> membership and visibility never propagate automatically across tenants.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h2 class="card-title">Workflow</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                Typical end-user flow from first access to document-based chat.
            </p>
            <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                <table class="table">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Step</th>
                            <th>What To Do</th>
                            <th>Where</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td><span class="badge badge-primary">1</span></td>
                            <td>Create your account and sign in to Harpyx.</td>
                            <td><a asp-page="/Welcome" class="link link-hover">Welcome</a></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><span class="badge badge-primary">2</span></td>
                            <td>Configure your personal LLM providers (Chat, RAG Embedding, optional OCR) and set defaults.</td>
                            <td><a asp-page="/Profile/Index" class="link link-hover">Profile</a></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><span class="badge badge-primary">3</span></td>
                            <td>Create or select the tenant context where your work should live.</td>
                            <td><a asp-page="/Tenants/Index" class="link link-hover">Tenants</a></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><span class="badge badge-primary">4</span></td>
                            <td>Invite members and assign roles for collaboration (if needed).</td>
                            <td><a asp-page="/Members/Index" class="link link-hover">Members</a></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><span class="badge badge-primary">5</span></td>
                            <td>Create workspaces in the selected tenant.</td>
                            <td><a asp-page="/Workspaces/Index" class="link link-hover">Workspaces</a></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><span class="badge badge-primary">6</span></td>
                            <td>Create projects in a workspace and define scope plus AI settings.</td>
                            <td><a asp-page="/Projects/Index" class="link link-hover">Projects</a></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><span class="badge badge-primary">7</span></td>
                            <td>Upload documents; Harpyx parses, extracts and prepares chunks for retrieval.</td>
                            <td><a asp-page="/Projects/Index" class="link link-hover">Project Details</a></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><span class="badge badge-primary">8</span></td>
                            <td>Indexing pipeline enriches content and enables semantic/keyword retrieval.</td>
                            <td><span class="text-base-content/70">Automatic background processing</span></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><span class="badge badge-primary">9</span></td>
                            <td>Use chat/Q&A against indexed project knowledge.</td>
                            <td><a asp-page="/Projects/Index" class="link link-hover">Project Details / Chat</a></td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="card h-full bg-base-100 shadow">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h2 class="card-title">Collaboration Across Tenants</h2>
                <div class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
                    You can work in multiple tenants. Membership can be granted directly or via invitation flows.
                </div>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-sm space-y-1">
                    <li>Create and manage your own tenants.</li>
                    <li>Invite users into a tenant and assign permissions with Members.</li>
                    <li>Be invited into other tenants and switch current tenant from the top-right menu.</li>
                    <li>Use Members to assign tenant roles and delegation permissions.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card h-full bg-base-100 shadow">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h2 class="card-title">Operational Checklist</h2>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-sm space-y-1">
                    <li>Confirm you are in the correct current tenant before creating/editing resources.</li>
                    <li>Use least-privilege role assignments for members.</li>
                    <li>Monitor ingestion/indexing health for document-heavy projects.</li>
                    <li>Validate provider credentials and quotas when chat/indexing are degraded.</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="pt-2">
                    <a asp-page="/Index" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">
                        <iconify-icon icon="mdi:view-dashboard-outline"></iconify-icon>
                        Go to Dashboard
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
